18 &= (b-a)x(d-c)\\
72 &= -(b-a)x(d+c)
\end{align*}
I divide the second equation by the first to eliminate $x$ and get a relation between $a$, $b$, $c$, and $d$:

\begin{align*}
\frac{72}{18} &= \frac{-(b-a)(d+c)}{(b-a)(d-c)}\\
-4 &= \frac{d+c}{d-c}
\end{align*}
