-4d + 4c &= d + c\\
-5d &= -3c\\
d &= \frac{3}{5}c
\end{align*}
Since $d$ and $c$ are positive integers, the only way this equation can hold is if $c$ is a multiple of 5 and $d$ a multiple of 3.
